Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams}.

Fry until the mince has browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as
it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the beef cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic
press{}).

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%grams}.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic to the beef and stir-fry, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @Tomato passata{1%carton}, @Soy sauce{15%milliliters},
@Gochujang paste{50%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the sauce{100%milliliters}
into the pan and stir to combine.

Bring the sauce up to the boil, add the green beans, then pop a #lid{} on the
pan (or cover with some #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven
until the mince is tender and the sauce has thickened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the beef cooks, pour the @Water for the rice{300%milliliters} into a
medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil.
Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the saucepan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

When everything's ready, remove the beef from the oven and stir through the
@BBQ sauce{32%grams}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of
water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls.

Top with your BBQ beef mince and sprinkle over the @Roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!